      "content": "so u said the benefits are \"generally proven\" but the social costs are \"real and growing.\" that sounds like the economic side is basically a settled fact and the social side is just an opinion or a feeling. if the data shows the money part is a win, why would any country actually want to keep doing it if it's tearing the social fabric apart?",
